modules.description: This module provides functions to create and manipulate UI components with specific data conversions, such as converting between integers, floats, strings, and their string representations. It supports constructing UI entries for individual values and lists, with configurable separators, and includes specialized components like checkbuttons and date pickers. Concrete use cases include building forms with typed input fields and structured data validation.

This module enables constructing form-based user interfaces with typed input handling and validation, operating on primitive types like integers, strings, and dates alongside their optional or list-wrapped variants. It provides structured UI components such as checkbuttons, date pickers, and label-or-text widgets, combined with container layouts like boxes, notebooks, and tables for organizing hierarchical interfaces with customizable styling. The design supports use cases like data entry forms with validation constraints, configuration dialogs requiring persistent serialization, and dynamic UI composition through widget coercion patterns.
